{"author":{"id":"5f5cd663a9920e640c6df6db8c058a79885cb73775cba0e434abf10948db44c0"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1647286216,"nonce":"vzoLBZalG69TFl88Vm0Izw9UM6M=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc4_nEVY","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/937#issuecomment-1067205976"},"message":"\u003e @AlmightyYakob Question: Sometimes, after uploading to a Zarr that already exists, the client may delete files from the Zarr that no longer exist on the local end. Should this deletion happen before or after POSTing to the \"ingest\" endpoint?\n\nGood question. The delete should happen before calling `ingest`, with a following call to `ingest` to recompute size, checksums, etc. An important note is that while an ingest is taking place, the zarr is \"locked\", meaning no files can be uploaded to or deleted from it. Similarly, if an upload of files is currently taking place, the zarr can't be ingested until those uploads are completed via the `POST /zarr/{zarr_id}/upload/complete` endpoint","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1647286222,"nonce":"cmExpyCsTytYz8yFfNCBnchTl0A=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALODBZtRc4_nEVYziGiayI"},"target":"e201bc00c08383fe1e6ceb3d4d8bf46790af86f634bbee47cdd08b6b2e52add1","message":"\u003e @AlmightyYakob Question: Sometimes, after uploading to a Zarr that already exists, the client may delete files from the Zarr that no longer exist on the local end. Should this deletion happen before or after POSTing to the \"ingest\" endpoint?\n\nGood question. The delete should happen before calling `ingest`, with a following call to `ingest` to recompute size, checksums, etc. An important note is that while an ingest is taking place, the zarr is \"locked\", meaning no files can be uploaded to or deleted from it. Similarly, if an upload of files is currently taking place, the zarr can't be ingested until those uploads are completed via the `POST /zarr/{zarr_id}/upload/complete` endpoint.","files":null}]}